-- New Zealand Central Bank Leaves Benchmark Rate Unchanged After Earthquake
-- B y   T i m   S m i t h
-- 2010-10-27T20:00:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/new-zealand-central-bank-leaves-benchmark-rate-unchanged-after-earthquake.html
The Reserve Bank of New Zealand left
its benchmark interest rate unchanged at 3 percent for a second
month after the nation’s worst earthquake in eight decades
slowed growth.  The central bank’s announcement, which was forecast by all
15 economists in a Bloomberg News survey, was made in a
statement today in Wellington.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Smith in Sydney at 
